The paper deals with anonymous group communication systems and their security, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of public key cryptography and knowledge proofs, which are topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of existing symmetric-key DC-nets, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and the detection of misbehavior, which is related to social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of the proposed system, which could be related to cybernetics (cs.CY).
